commentary: Murtagh to Williams, OUT short ball outside the off stump. Williams was set up for the shot that he played - pull. He lofts it to McCarthy at deep midwicket. He didn't need to run a lot to take the catch. That's poor awareness of the match situation by Williams. When a fielder is placed for exactly that shot, one should get their eye in before thinking of clearing that fielder. Also the pace of Murtagh is such that Williams had to impart a lot of power on his own to get it over the ropes

commentary: Cremer to Stirling, OUT what a co-incidence! Zimbabwe and Ireland both have a run-out on 26.6 overs! Good length ball outside the off stump. Stirling defends it to the off side and sets off for what he deems to be a single. Wilson refuses but Stirling is close to Wilson then the stumps. So, it's obvious that Stirling would be struggling. He is couple of feet out. Ervine was out on 26.6 over for Zimbabwe
